## What Does a 2 Carat Princess Cut Diamond Cost in {{year}}?

At 2 carats, the price range is wide and the buying decision is more complex than at 1ct. The gap between the cheapest and most expensive 2ct GIA princess cut on Blue Nile is $17,762 — driven entirely by color, clarity, and specific proportions within the Ideal Cut designation.

I am **Farzana Hasan**, GIA-certified diamond expert and author of the [princess cut diamond guide](/princess-cut-diamond). Here is the complete 2ct princess inventory audit from Blue Nile, every stone listed with its grade, price, and direct link. Then I explain what each tier means, where the value breaks down, and which stones are worth buying.

